</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.5.2. ">Sold to Block (SAP Blocks)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>From account record page, go to 'Related' tab and there we can see 'Customer BAG Contact Associations'. Open the related 'Business Account Group' (BAG) record. <span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);">#review this once</span>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-57-58.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>The related 'BAG' record opens in a new subtab. Open 'Related' tab in BAG record tab and we can see the 'Customer CMFs' associated with the contact in 'Customer BAG CMF Associations'</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-58-13.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Click on any "Customer CMF" to open the corresponding record detail page. Navigate to 'related' tab and there we can see 'Customer Partners (Partner CMF)' records and their corresponding role code.</li>
  <li>If the 'Customer CMF' record has a related 'Customer Partner' record with role code "<a href="#handytip-27412159773918987">AG</a>", then Customer CMF record is eligible as a 'sold to' CMF.<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="72e53dc0-9a31-42e1-873d-ce36ce77c5ce" ac:name="handy-tip" ac:schema-version="1">
      <ac:parameter ac:name="id">27412159773918987</ac:parameter>
      <ac:parameter ac:name="atlassian-macro-output-type">INLINE</ac:parameter>
      <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
          <span style="color:var(--ds-text,#000000);">Sold-to party</span>
        </p>
      </ac:rich-text-body>
    </ac:structured-macro>
  </li>
  <li>This means that we have a valid sold to record for creation of a R4C case.</li>
  <li>All 'Customer CMF' records which have a related 'Customer Partner' record (with role code AG) can be selected as sold to.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-58-28.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>There are 3 types of SAP blocks which are <strong>Central Order Block</strong>, <strong>Central Billing Block</strong> &amp; <strong>Central Delivery Block.</strong>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-58-43.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Check if there is any Central Order Block, Central Billing Block &amp; Central Delivery Block. Otherwise, directly check the blocks at Sales Area Level. (No need to check other blocks at CMF level) <span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);"># Add SOQLs where we can do that</span>
  </li>
  <li>If <strong>central order block</strong> is present i.e., (Customer Central Order Block = '01' or '02' or '03' or '99') it is a hard stop and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information.</li>
  <li>If <strong>central billing block</strong> is present and billing block value (Customer Central Billing Block="99" or "12") then it is a hard stop, and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information.</li>
  <li>If <strong>Central Delivery block</strong> is present and Delivery block value (Central Delivery block = "99") then it is a hard stop and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="33edb836-9723-4bae-9d35-9b73ad29d2c9" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <ul>
      <li>In Case creation, If any of the SAP Block is available at Sold to CMF level then that Sold To CMF will not be displayed in the Sold To selection.</li>
      <li>In Case Edit, If any of the SAP Block is available at Sold to CMF level then on click of Case Edit button, it will display an error toast message &amp; not able to Edit the case.</li>
    </ul>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
