<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.6. ">Request Header Details</h2>
<ul>
  <li>User should fill in all the mandatory fields which are marked with the red color asterisk symbol (<span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);">*</span>) and until all mandatory fields are entered, next button should be disabled.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-1-35.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Contact Name &amp; Account Name will be auto populated as Hyperlinks. The selected Service Type is shown as the text field.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Sold To:</strong> All the 'Customer CMF' records which are related to the account which have a related 'Customer Partner' record (with role code : AG) can be selected as valid sold to.</li>
  <li>For selecting Sold To, we have a wild card search functionality which makes it easy to search and get the required CMF value instead of going through all the values in a dropdown.</li>
  <li>Based on the Selected Sold To Value, all other data will be fetched for other dropdowns.</li>
  <li>When Sold To is selected, all the other details are auto populated based on the selected 'Sold to' value. Values are auto populated based on the most recent case created using that particular 'Sold To'.</li>
  <li>All other fields in Request header details are dropdowns, if any dropdown contains a single value, it would be auto populated when agent selects a value on dependent dropdown for that dropdown.</li>
  <li>Sold To Address values are determined and populated from the 'Customer Physical Address' records which are related to selected Sold To CMF having address type as 'Sold to'.</li>
  <li>From Agent UI, we can see the address records related to selected Sold To: Go to the sold to 'Customer CMF record' &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; See the address Type as 'AG/WE/RG'. All the active addresses would be displayed for user to choose from.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:width="924">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-1-48.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>The available sales areas for the selected Sold To are shown in the "Sales Area" (Sales Area= Sales org Code –Sales org Name/Distributional Code-Distribution channel name, e.g., EU02-U.K./02-Industrial Disti) dropdown.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Ship To:</strong> All the 'Customer CMF' records which are related to the account which have a related 'Customer Partner' record (with role code : WE) can be selected as valid sold to.</li>
  <li>These values are dependent on the Selected Sold To &amp; Sales Area. Hence, when the Sold To/Sales Area is changed the other fields should be refreshed/reset.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Note:</strong> We have wildcard search functionality present for 'Ship To' field also, which works similar to 'Sold To' search.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Remedy:</strong> For Service type "Exception" the possible remedy values are 'Credit', 'NPR-Credit'. Agent can select one value from the dropdown.</li>
  <li>The Address available for the selected Sold To/ Ship To are displayed in the dropdown.</li>
  <li>The contacts available for the selected Addresses are displayed in the dropdown.</li>
</ul>
