<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.7. ">Collection Details</h2>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.7.1. ">For Remedy = Credit</h3>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-3-6.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent should be unable to select anything in 'Collection details' section as it will be disabled until all the required fields in the 'Request Header Details' section are filled.</li>
  <li>Once all the required fields in 'Required header details' are filled, agent would be able to select 'Return to Customer Address' value from the dropdown in 'Collection Details'. These address are determined from the Sold To 'Customer CMF' record.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Return to Customer Address</strong>: Options are determined and populated from the 'Customer Physical Address' records which are related to selected Sold To CMF having address type as 'Return To Customer'.</li>
  <li>Agent have search option from the dropdown to select Return to Customer address, can search by Name, Country, State &amp; Postal Code</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-3-16.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>To see the address records related to selected Sold To: Go to the sold to 'Customer CMF record' &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; See the address Type as 'Return To Customer'. All the active address records would be displayed for agent to choose from.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Return to Customer Contact</strong>: These contact values are fetched based on the selected 'Return to Customer Address'.</li>
  <li>To see the contact records related to selected 'Return to Customer Address': Go to the sold to 'Customer CMF record' &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; Open the selected 'Return To Customer' address record &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Physical Address Contacts. All the active contact records would be displayed for agent to choose from.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Freight Type:</strong> Once 'Return to Customer Address' is selected, Freight type values are determined and populated from <strong>'Sales Freight Determination Matrix'</strong>.</li>
  <li>The values are populated from filtering the matrix records by passing Remedy, Service Type, Return Reason, Geo, Country (RTC Address Country) fields in the matrix. If no record is found for above combination, 'Return reason' is excluded and details are fetched again.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Freight Type-IMF:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>If the agent selects the freight type as IMF (Intel Managed Freight), or if IMF is auto populated (In case of only one freight type value), then agent needs to select Collection Address, Collection contact &amp; also Collection date are mandatory to proceed further.</li>
      <li>After selecting the Collection Address, then collection date field is enabled, and date is auto populated based on the Sales Geo lead time as shown below.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:width="905">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-3-29.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Collection Date</strong> is auto populated based on <strong>Geo Lead Time Matrix</strong> for IMF.  <span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);">#Remove this section as we are not calling anymore</span>
  </li>
  <li>For APAC / APJ - 5 days are considered as 'Lead Time'. Here the 5th day from current day/case creation day will be auto populated in the collection date. Apart from that the 4th day would be enabled for agent to choose from and the next 8 days would also be enabled for a total of 10 enabled days. These dates are all excluding holidays and weekends.</li>
  <li>For all other regions -- 'Lead Time' is 3 days. Therefore, 3rd day from current day would be auto populated, 2nd day would be enabled along with the next 8 days succeeding 'Lead Time' excluding holidays &amp; weekends.</li>
  <li>Example - Let Case creation date is 14th Mar 2023, the date auto populated for Geo APJ would be 22nd Mar 2023 if there is no holiday for the selected collection Address. If there is holiday for that country on 22nd Mar 2023, then it would be auto populated as 23rd Mar 2023</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Freight Type-CRF (Customer Routed Freight):</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>If the user selects the freight type as CRF (Customer Routed Freight), the collection date, Return to customer address &amp; Return to customer contact fields are mandatory to proceed further.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Collection date</strong> will auto-populate to the current day/case creation day as soon as the user selects freight type as "CRF" and all the succeeding days would be enabled for the agent to choose from including holidays and weekends.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="16a72708-c8c7-42fa-bece-db4ec3b840e1" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>'Collection date' would be reset if the case is edited and the collection date is not equal to current date.</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Collection Address:</strong> Collection address and collection contact fields are only mandatory if Freight type is selected as IMF. Collection address values are determined and fetched similar to 'Return to Customer Address' values.</li>
  <li>The options are determined and populated from the 'Customer Physical Address' records which are related to selected Sold To CMF having address type as 'Collection'.</li>
  <li>Agent have search option to select Collection address from the dropdown, can search by Name, Country, State &amp; Postal Code.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-3-43.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Also the addresses are filtered based on the Geo value of the selected Return to customer address.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Collection Contact:</strong> These contacts are fetched based on the selected 'Collection Address'.</li>
  <li>To see the contact records related to selected 'Collection Address': Go to the sold to 'Customer CMF record' &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; Open the selected 'Collection Address' record &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Physical Address Contacts. All the active contacts would be displayed for agent to choose from.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Origin Bond:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>If the selected RTC/Collection Address belongs to India/China then only User can see the Origin Bonded option in UI &amp; this value is selected as 'Non-Bonded' by default. Customer can select 'Bonded' value according to the requirements.</li>
      <li>If the selected RTC/Collection Address does not belong to India/China then Origin Bonded option is not visible in UI &amp; by default it will be considered as 'Non-Bonded'.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:width="915">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-3-57.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Return Location:</strong> Return location value is determined from 'Sales Return Location Matrix' by using the selected Remedy, Service Type, Sold To CMF, Bonded Zone Indicator, Country (IMF- Collection Country, CRF - RTC Country)</li>
  <li>If no match is found with above combination, then Sold To CMF is excluded and Return Location value fetched again. If still no record is found, then it's a hard stop and agent is notified by relevant error toast message.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:width="922">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-4-8.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
