<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.8.2. ">Purchase/Sales Order Search</h3>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-6-11.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>By using the above interface, agent can search for line items using single or multiple comma separated 'PO Numbers' or 'SO Numbers'.</li>
  <li>On click of Search button, date range is automatically selected 5 years in the backend.</li>
  <li>Agent can reset the search data by clicking on the Reset button.</li>
  <li>After agent enters the PO or SO number(s), that data is sent to 'ECA View via Orchestration layer' by clicking on the "Search" button to get line items from 'ECA View via Orchestration layer'.</li>
  <li>If no response is obtained, it is a hard stop and agent is notified via error toast message 'Records not found/Please check your PO number which you entered'.</li>
  <li>The line-item data obtained as response from API is again validated in database using Item Type 'FERT' or 'KITS' check. If Item type of line items is not 'FERT' or 'KITS', those line items are disabled.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-6-30.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can select the line items from valid line-item data, at which point 'Next' and 'Save for Later' buttons would be enabled for agent to proceed to next step 'Product Validation'.</li>
  <li>Agent can reset the line-item data by clicking on the "Reset" button.</li>
  <li>Agent can see the "Delete Line item" column in Line item table.</li>
  <li>In Case creation, on click of 'Delete' button the Line item will be removed from the Line item list.</li>
  <li>In Case Edit, on click of 'Delete' button the Line item will get unselected from the Line item list &amp; that Line item will not proceed to next steps.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="545b21bc-4c7a-4028-b86b-52091f9aa7c4" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>Users can proceed only with up to 999 lines. If more than 999 lines are present after search/upload and clicking Next, an error appears: "You can only proceed with 999 lines".</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.8.3. ">Product Search</h3>
<ul>
  <li>When agent selects the product search option, he is presented with the following interface where agent has to select one option from the 2 options given:</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-6-47.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can search with one or more MM or CPN by selecting respective radio button.</li>
  <li>After agent selects one option and enters the related data, he can get the related line items data by clicking on the "Search" button.</li>
  <li>If <strong>agent searches using MM</strong>, the data inputted by the agent would be validated in the SF database and then valid MM numbers are sent to MM-CPN API to get the respective CPN numbers for the MMs.</li>
  <li>If <strong>agent searches using CPN</strong>, data is sent first to MM-CPN API to get the required MMs and all the valid MMs obtained will again be validated in the database to get product details.</li>
  <li>The line-item data obtained as response from API is again validated using Item Type 'FERT' or 'KITS'. If Item type of line items is not 'FERT' or 'KITS', those line items are disabled.</li>
  <li>Then the valid line items would be displayed in the table with related product information obtained from database.</li>
  <li>The line items which fail in validation would be shown in disabled state and validation error would be shown on 'i' icon in validation column.</li>
  <li>If all entered data fails validation, it is a hard stop and agent is notified via error toast message.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-7-2.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can select the required line items and then should click on 'PO History' button to get the required PO data for the selected line items (validation from POH API).</li>
  <li>While validating from POH API initially the data range would be Current date -- 5 years.</li>
  <li>If we get the PO numbers for all the required line items, agent can directly proceed further.</li>
  <li>If we don't get the PO numbers for all the selected line items, we will show an error "PO history check failed" as shown below.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-7-16.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<p>
  <u>Validate PO:</u>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can also enter the PO numbers manually in the input box for each valid line item. The entered PO number would be validated when clicking on the Validate PO button.</li>
  <li>Validate PO Number line will be bypassed at PO History step; if the line failed at the Validate PO step, the line item will be Hardstop.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-7-32.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Until PO validation is done, agent cannot proceed further. If all entered data fails validation, it is a hard stop and agent is notified via error toast message.</li>
  <li>Once PO History check is done, Agent can proceed to next step by clicking on 'Next'. Agent would be navigated to the 'Product validation screen'.</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.8.4. ">Bulk Upload</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Along with search functionality, agent can also upload line items data by using 'Bulk upload' functionality.<span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);"> # add all the relevant validations for bulk upload </span>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-7-45.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent is provided the option to download the CSV template and enter the required line-item data.</li>
  <li>Then agent can upload the file by either clicking on the upload file button and selecting the file, or he can drag and drop the CSV file on the 'drop files' area to upload it.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <u>Template sample:</u>
</p>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-7-58.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Here for each line-item data entered, MM number or CPN number should be mandatorily entered along with Box Condition and Return quantity.</li>
  <li>All other fields are optional, and data entered will be mapped to the particular line-item column in respective stages.</li>
  <li>If agent wants to specify 'Return Package Conditions', the acceptable values are 'Outer Box Opened -- Product Unsealed', 'Outer Box Opened -- Product sealed' and 'Box closed -- Factory sealed'. All other values would be invalid.</li>
  <li>Once agent uploads the CSV file, he has to click on 'Validate' button for line-item data to be read and validated.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <u>Validation Scenarios:</u>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If an empty file or a file with format other than '.csv' is uploaded, agent is notified with error toast message.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:width="870">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-8-9.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>The agent can upload only 750 lines per bulk upload. It is the maximum limit, and more than 750 lines cannot be uploaded at once.</li>
  <li>The agent can upload only 750 lines per bulk upload. Since the case submission limit is 999 lines, the remaining 249 lines can be uploaded after the initial 750 lines are processed. <span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);">#ISSUE</span>
  </li>
  <li>Uploading more than 750 lines through bulk upload will show an error message saying: "Please search/upload a file with a maximum of 750 lines only."</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-8-23.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If the file is missing any required field for any Line item, agent is notified with an error in Toast Message as well as an Error Description Screen will be shown right under the upload UI as below, where agent is notified with line numbers of the errors in the file and there is an option to download the file by clicking on Bulk_Upload_Results.csv, and in the file we can also see the error message attributed to each line item in an additional column, if any exists.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-9-33.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If no validation errors are present and line-item data containing only MM numbers is uploaded, data is fetched using MM-CPN API to get the respective CPN numbers for the entered MM numbers.</li>
  <li>Similarly, if line-item data containing only CPN numbers is uploaded, data is fetched using MM-CPN API to get the respective MM numbers for the entered CPN numbers.</li>
  <li>If data uploaded is a combination of MM numbers and CPNs, we get the respective required CPNs and MMs.</li>
  <li>After uploading and validating the data, Agent will receive a pop-up template that shows the MM number replaced with another MM number, as shown below.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-9-48.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Next the MM data which is entered or obtained is validated against the database including validation using Item Type 'FERT' or 'KITS'. If Item type of line items is not 'FERT' or 'KITS', those line items are disabled.</li>
  <li>For all the valid line-items, related product data is fetched and displayed as shown below.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-10-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can select the required line items and then should click on 'PO History' button to get the required PO data for the selected line items (validation from POH API).</li>
  <li>While validating from POH API initially the data range would be Current date -- 5 years.</li>
  <li>If we get the PO numbers for all the required line items, agent can directly proceed further.</li>
  <li>If we don't get the PO numbers for all the selected line items, we will show an error message.</li>
  <li>Agent can also enter the PO numbers manually in the input box for each valid line item. The entered PO number would be validated from API.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-10-13.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Until PO validation is done, agent cannot proceed further. If all entered data fails validation, it is a hard stop and agent is notified via error toast message.</li>
  <li>Once PO History check is done, Agent can proceed to next step by clicking on 'Next'. Agent would be navigated to the 'Credit Price validation screen'.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="6adf0e5b-6518-4966-a452-fa1be3de605c" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>Users can proceed only with up to 999 lines. If more than 999 lines are present after search/upload and clicking Next, an error appears: "You can only proceed with 999 lines".</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-10-26.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="107d2f3f-93a4-4c36-a147-0dd45787ff94" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>After clicking <strong>Next</strong> after <strong>PO History</strong>, <strong>Disti Product status check validation</strong> will happen here and the following Product status check validation will be done.</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ul>
  <li>The following Disti Channel Product Status Codes are allowed for Agent Case creation: <strong>AC, RS, EN, OB, RP, RT, QR, NO, E2</strong>
  </li>
  <li>The following Disti Channel Product Status Codes are 'not allowed' for Agent Case creation: <strong>PA, NI</strong>
  </li>
  <li>When we try to create a case with product status <strong>PA</strong> and <strong>NI</strong> it will be a Hardstop and will show an error message saying "Current status is PA" and for NI "current status is NI"</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-10-44.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-10-56.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If the Product status is not valid or empty (null), it will display an error message saying "No valid product status were found"</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-11-11.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="0bbb4a01-d9bd-4dee-96f1-e0c3ddc68ee8" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>On click of 'Next' button if Return Reason is 'Exception Return', Agent needs to select <strong>only one line item</strong> to proceed to further steps, else it is a hard stop to proceed further.</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-11-27.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If the agent is in Credit price step and wants to change the line item, he should deselect the current line item in step 2 and go back to the search page to add a new line item.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-11-40.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If agent adds the new line item, then on click of next button, if the agent has not deselected the previous line item which is in step-2, he will be notified to clear the line items in step-2 first to proceed with adding the new one.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-11-53.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Note:</strong>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If Return Reason is <strong>Exception return</strong> where Price can change, it can be changed to zero (<strong>0</strong>).</li>
  <li>If not Zero (<strong>0</strong>), Price should be the same which is fetched from <strong>PO price</strong> to create a successful case.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-12-5.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.8.5. ">Credit Price Validation</h3>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-12-23.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>In "Credit Price Validation" section, agent can see "Get Credit Price" button enabled for all selected line items.</li>
  <li>Enter the Return Quantity for each line item as it is a mandatory field. Return Po &amp; Debit Reference number are optional fields.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:width="906">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-12-37.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Once agent clicks on 'Get Credit Price' button:<ul>
      <li>If the Distribution channel of the case that is being created is 01, or Return Reason is Exception Return or Quarterly Exception Return, then the Unit Price of the Line item will be determined by the SalesOrderLineNetPriceAmt attribute value of POH API.</li>
      <li>If the Distribution channel is anything other than 01-Direct, i.e., 02-Industrial Distribution or 03-Retail, then the Unit Price of every Line Item will be fetched by making a callout to PIC API by passing required Parameters (selected MMs, selected Sold to CMF and sales org).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>'Net credit Value' of each valid line item is calculated as 'Return Quantity' * 'Credit Price' and is displayed in the 'Net credit value' column.</li>
  <li>If no credit price value is fetched from PIC API, then the agent has the option to enter the price and Reason in the input columns.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <strong>PIC System Price Zero Scenarios:</strong>
</p>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-12-51.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>The agent needs to fill in the 'Reason for the price change' field if he enters the credit price manually.</li>
  <li>Without filling out the Credit Price and Reason for price change, the agent can't proceed to the next step with that line-item; these validations will be checked on click of "Save and view summary" button.</li>
  <li>If the agent enters the credit price and Reason for price change for all required line-items.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-13-3.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>This is a mandatory field to proceed further. Once the agent fills in the Reason for Price Change and clicks on Submit, the case will be created, and the user will be navigated to the View Summary page.</li>
  <li>Agent also has the option to select the 'Box Condition' of each line item.<span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);"> #Review this once</span>
  </li>
  <li>After successfully obtaining the credit price, the 'Save &amp; View Summary' button is enabled so the agent can move to the view page.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="ad9e6d8c-f53d-416a-af55-e6e4249b716f" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>If Return Reason is Quarterly Exception or GRL Exception Return, agent needs to select Box condition value <strong>mandatorily</strong>. If not, he cannot proceed further; this validation will be checked on click of 'Save and View summary' button and agent is notified by a toast message.</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-13-20.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="fca54f18-999b-41b4-9dc6-ad2a10bb14f0" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>If Return Reason is Quarterly Exception, agent can always change the price which is fetched from the POH system.</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-13-32.png"/>
  </ac:image>
