<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.9. ">Line Items Section when Remedy is NPR-Credit</h2>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.1. ">Search/Upload Screen</h3>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-13-47.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Search By option is further divided into:<ul>
      <li>Purchase/Sales Order search using:<ul>
          <li>PO Number (Purchase Order Number)</li>
          <li>SO Number (Sales Order Number)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Product Search using:<ul>
          <li>MM (Material Master identification)</li>
          <li>CPN (Customer Part Number)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.2. ">Purchase/Sales Order Search</h3>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-14-3.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>By using the above interface, agent can search for line items using single or multiple comma separated 'PO Numbers' or 'SO Numbers'.</li>
  <li>On click of Search button, back-end date range is set to current date - 5 years, and proceeds with the search.</li>
  <li>Agent can reset the search data by clicking on the Reset button.</li>
  <li>After agent enters the PO or SO number(s), that data is sent to 'ECA View via Orchestration layer' by clicking on the "Search" button to get line items from 'ECA View via Orchestration layer'.</li>
  <li>If no response is obtained, it is a hard stop and agent is notified via error toast message 'Records not found/Please check your PO number which you entered'.</li>
  <li>The line-item data obtained as response from API is again validated in database using Item Type 'FERT' or 'KITS' check. If Item type of line items is not 'FERT' or 'KITS', those line items are disabled.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-14-16.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can select the line items from valid line-item data, at which point 'Next' and 'Save for Later' buttons would be enabled for agent to proceed to next step 'Warranty Entitlement Check'.</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.3. ">Product Search</h3>
<ul>
  <li>When agent selects the product search option, he is presented with the following interface where agent has to select one option to search with from the 2 options given:</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-14-28.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can search with one or more MM or CPN by selecting respective radio button.</li>
  <li>After agent selects one option and enters the related data, he can get the related line items data by clicking on the "Search" button.</li>
  <li>If <strong>agent searches using MM</strong>, the data inputted by the agent would be validated in the SF database and then valid MM numbers are sent to MM-CPN API to get the respective CPN numbers for the MMs.</li>
  <li>If <strong>agent searches using CPN</strong>, data is sent first to MM-CPN API to get the required MMs and all the valid MMs obtained will again be validated in the database to get product details.</li>
  <li>The line-item data obtained as response from API is again validated using Item Type 'FERT' or 'KITS'. If Item type of line items is not 'FERT' or 'KITS', those line items are disabled.</li>
  <li>Then the valid line items would be displayed in the table with related product information obtained from database.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-14-39.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<p>After getting the line item, if we click on Next button it will validate as shown below</p>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-14-52.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="b2587a93-f350-448c-8429-9eabc5865bdf" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>Here, the above line item does not display the box condition in the table only if remedy type is "NPR-Credit".</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ul>
  <li>The line items which fail in validation would be shown in disabled state and validation error would be shown on 'i' icon in validation column.</li>
  <li>If all entered data fails validation, it is a hard stop and agent is notified via error toast message.</li>
  <li>Agent can also enter the PO numbers manually in the input box for each valid line item. The entered PO number would be validated from POH API in step 3.</li>
  <li>Agent can select the required line items and then should click on 'Next' for further steps, or Agent can click on Save for Later to save the case at the present step.</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.4. ">Bulk Upload</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Along with search functionality, agent can also upload the line items data by using 'Bulk upload' functionality.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-15-5.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent is provided the option to download the CSV template and enter the required line-item data.</li>
  <li>Then agent can upload the file by either clicking on the upload file button and selecting the file, or he can also drag and drop the CSV file near the 'drop files' area to upload it.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <u>Template sample:</u>
</p>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-15-17.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Here for each line-item data entered, MM number or CPN number should be mandatorily entered along with quantity.</li>
  <li>All other fields are optional, and data entered will be mapped to the particular line-item column in further stages respectively.</li>
  <li>If agent wants to specify 'Return Package Conditions', the acceptable values are 'Outer Box Opened -- Product Unsealed' and 'Box closed -- Factory sealed'. All other values would be invalid.</li>
  <li>Once agent uploads the CSV file, he has to click on 'Validate' button for line-item data to be read and validated.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <u>Validation Scenarios:</u>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If an empty file or a file with format other than '.csv' is uploaded, agent is notified with error toast message.</li>
</ul>
<p>i<ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-15-29.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>The agent can upload only 750 lines per bulk upload. It is the maximum limit, and more than 750 lines cannot be uploaded at once.</li>
  <li>The agent can upload only 750 lines per bulk upload. Since the case submission limit is 999 lines, the remaining 249 lines can be uploaded after the initial 750 lines are processed.</li>
  <li>Uploading more than 750 lines through bulk upload will show an error message saying: "Please search/upload a file with a maximum of 750 lines only."</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-15-47.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If no validation errors are present and line-item data containing only MM numbers is uploaded, data is fetched using MM-CPN API to get the respective CPN numbers for the entered MM numbers.</li>
  <li>Similarly, if line-item data containing only CPN numbers is uploaded, data is fetched using MM-CPN API to get the respective MM numbers for the entered CPN numbers.</li>
  <li>If data uploaded is a combination of MM numbers and CPNs, we get the respective required CPNs and MMs.</li>
  <li>If data uploaded has one MM Number replaced with another CPN number, after uploading the data and validating, the User will get a pop-up template that shows the MM number replaced with another MM number, as shown below.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-16-3.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Next the MM data which is entered or obtained is validated against the database including validation using Item Type 'FERT' or 'KITS'. If Item type of line items is not 'FERT' or 'KITS', those line items are disabled.</li>
  <li>For all the valid line-items, related product data is fetched and displayed as shown below.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-16-14.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can also enter the PO numbers manually in the input box for each valid line item. The entered PO number would be validated from API.</li>
  <li>Agent can proceed to next step by clicking on 'Next'. Agent would be navigated to the 'Warranty Entitlement screen'.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="befda4c8-9bb6-42d9-88a8-568c92fccb10" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>Users can proceed only with up to 999 lines. If more than 999 lines are present after search/upload and clicking Next, an error appears: "You can only proceed with 999 lines".</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-16-43.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.5. ">Warranty Entitlement Check</h3>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-16-55.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can enter the Product Unique Id for the line items in the UI.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-17-7.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>On click of 'Warranty entitlement check' button, we are checking <strong>Return Quantity Greater Than One</strong>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-17-24.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<p>When ULT is entered for any line item by Agent/Customer and the return quantity of the line is greater than <strong>1</strong>, the system will automatically change the return quantity to <strong>1</strong> by default. If the user wants to process the particular MM having a line for multiple quantity, the user will then need to add respective ULT values for the remaining quantity.</p>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-17-40.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>After clicking the <strong>Warranty Entitlement Check</strong> button, the system will check if the return quantity has changed after entering the ULT for any line item having Return Qty &gt; 1.</li>
  <li>If Return Quantity has changed after entering the ULT, a pop-up window will appear, allowing the user to add ULTs for the remaining quantity using the <strong>bulk upload</strong> option.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-17-52.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If the user doesn't want to add ULTs for the remaining quantity, he can click <strong>Proceed without New Lines</strong> to skip this step. The system will perform the Warranty validations for existing lines and display the result.</li>
  <li>If the user wants to add more lines for any MM which had quantity &gt; 1 before giving ULT, he has to provide ULTs for the remaining quantity using the process below.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <strong>Downloading the ULT Template</strong>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>User should download the template file by clicking <strong>Download Template</strong>. A CSV file will be downloaded, which contains three columns:</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-18-3.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>MM</strong>: This is the product name.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>ULT</strong>: This is the unique identifier for the product.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Line Identifier</strong>: This is used to match the data to the correct line item (Backend purpose)</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="e4b0d7db-7f59-4fef-813f-ec650faaf332" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Important</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>Do not change any column headers, add or delete rows, or modify existing data in the template. You only need to fill in the ULT for each MM item.</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<p>
  <strong>Uploading the ULT File</strong>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Once the user has added the ULTs required for additional lines, the user should upload the file by clicking <strong>Upload Files</strong>. The system will check the file for the following:</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-18-18.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ol>
  <li>No changes to the column headers.</li>
  <li>No new rows added or existing rows deleted/modified.</li>
  <li>Each ULT must be filled out, with a length between 6 to 40 characters, and no duplicates allowed.</li>
</ol>
<ul>
  <li>If there are any errors, they will be shown on the screen. User can download the error file, make corrections, and upload it again.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-18-32.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Validation and Next Steps</strong>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>If the file is correct, the system will upload it successfully. After clicking <strong>Validate</strong>, new lines will be added to the table, and the system will perform further checks, such as making sure there are no duplicate ULTs and fetching the warranty details from EH API.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-18-46.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Local ULT duplicate check: In SF, any open case has the same ULT.</li>
  <li>API duplicate check for scrap: In EH API, checks whether any particular ULT is duplicate or is scrapped.</li>
  <li>When the user gets the below popup, the user needs to adjust other ULTs and proceed to create the Case.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:width="889">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-19-0.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>The entered product unique ids of the line items will be validated in the Entitlement API.</li>
  <li>In response we will be checking whether Product Unique Id is valid or not and whether the status is Active.</li>
  <li>If the Product Unique Id is not valid or if the status is not active, those line items will be disabled in the UI.</li>
  <li>The line items which don't have a product unique id will bypass the validations of checking valid Product Unique Id, Active status and Extended warranty line items.<span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);"> # extended warranty is not in IAO remove this</span>
  </li>
  <li>If there are any extended warranty line items for the given product unique Id, those line items will be added into the UI under the parent line item.</li>
  <li>Validating the Extended warranty lines based on below conditions:<ul>
      <li>The Extended warranty Product Unique Id should be valid.</li>
      <li>The Extended Warranty End date should be greater than the current date.</li>
      <li>The main line item of the Extended line should be valid without any errors.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>If any of the conditions has failed, the extended line item will be disabled in the UI.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-19-15.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can proceed with required line items to the next step.</li>
  <li>On click of 'Next' button, the line items will be validated using the required field matrix logic, and if any of the ULT, CPN fields in specific line items are required, then the User will be notified by a toast message and he has to enter the mandatory fields to proceed further.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="3bb6ab13-dd9f-46e5-9e4e-2c266e0364e5" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>After clicking <strong>Next</strong> after <strong>Warranty entitlement check</strong>, <strong>Disti Product status check validation</strong> will happen here and the following Product status check validation will be done.</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ul>
  <li>The following Disti Channel Product Status Codes are allowed for Agent Case creation: <strong>AC, RS, EN, OB, RP, RT, QR, NO, E2</strong>
  </li>
  <li>The following Disti Channel Product Status Codes are not allowed for Agent Case creation: <strong>PA, NI</strong>
  </li>
  <li>When we try to create a case with product status <strong>PA</strong> and <strong>NI</strong> it will be a Hardstop and will show an error message saying "Current status is PA" and for NI "current status is NI"</li>
</ul>
