<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.9.7. ">Credit Price Validation</h3>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-20-41.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>In the "Credit Price Validation" step, agent can see the "Credit Price Validation" button enabled for all selected line items.</li>
  <li>Enter the Return Quantity for each line item as it is a mandatory field. Return Po &amp; Debit Reference number are optional fields.</li>
  <li>Once agent clicks on the 'Credit Price Validation' button:<ul>
      <li>If the Distribution channel of the case that is being created is 01, then the Unit Price of the Line item will be determined by the SalesOrderLineNetPriceAmt attribute value of POH API.</li>
      <li>If the Distribution channel is anything apart from 01-Direct, then the Unit Price of every line item will be fetched by making a callout to PIC API by passing required parameters (selected MMs, selected Sold to CMF and sales org).<span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);"> # review</span>
      </li>
      <li>If no credit price value is fetched from PIC API, then the agent has the option to enter the price and Reason in the input columns.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <strong>PIC System Price Zero Scenarios:</strong>
</p>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-21-0.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>The agent needs to fill in the 'Reason for the price change' field if he enters the credit price manually. <span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);"> # this is another place that is referencing custom settings check the value and make the corresponding changes</span>
  </li>
  <li>Without filling out the Credit Price and Reason for price change, the agent can't proceed to the next step with that line-item; these validations will be checked on click of "Save and view summary" button.</li>
  <li>If the agent enters the credit price and Reason for price change for all required line-items.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-21-15.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>This is a mandatory field to proceed further. Once the agent fills in the Reason for Price Change and clicks on Submit, the case will be created, and the user will be navigated to the View Summary page.</li>
  <li>'Net credit Value' of each valid line item is calculated as 'Return Quantity' * 'Credit Price' and displayed in the 'Net credit value' column.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-21-32.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>After successfully obtaining the credit price, the 'Save &amp; View Summary' button is enabled so the agent can move to the view page.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.10. ">View Summary Page</h2>
<ul>
  <li>On clicking the button, agent is navigated to the 'Save &amp; View summary'/'Ready to Submit' page.</li>
  <li>Here agent can see all the case details briefly and confirm if everything is correct before he can submit the case.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image>
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-21-50.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Agent can see "Edit", "Cancel" and "Submit" buttons.</li>
  <li>In case of any soft blocks (SAP blocks or other), the 'Submit' button will be disabled and agent would be notified by a toast message about the presence of soft blocks.</li>
  <li>Then agent can edit the case again or continue and submit the case if no soft blocks are present.</li>
  <li>On click of the Submit button, the case is submitted with case status as 'Pending Approval' and agent is redirected to the 'Case Detail Page'.</li>
  <li>If agent clicks on Cancel then the case is saved with "Open, Unsubmitted" status and agent is redirected to the related 'Case Detail Page'.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="b99ec9e5-806e-401c-909a-c134071dd3cb" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note: Email Approval Scenario</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <ul>
      <li>For Exception Intake, every case must first be approved by an external approver to get 'RMA Authorized'.</li>
      <li>Scenarios:<ul>
          <li>If total price overridden for line items is greater than 25k, then first the 'L3 Approver' needs to approve the particular line items before the case is sent to the External approver.</li>
          <li>If the L3 approver declines the approval request, then Case status is set to 'Declined' and external approval will not be triggered.</li>
          <li>In case of price override less than 25k, on load of the 'View Summary page', the email of the external approver is fetched from the 'Approval Matrix' by sending sold to CMF, remedy, return reason, service type, distribution channel and sales org along with net credit price.</li>
          <li>If Remedy is <strong>'Credit'</strong> and Return Reason is <strong>'Exception Return'</strong>, on load of the 'View Summary page', the email of the external approver is fetched from the 'ILM Approval Matrix' by sending sold to CMF, service type, approver source, Location Geography along with valid 'From' and 'To' dates. <span style="color:var(--ds-background-accent-red-subtle,#f87168);">#this is controlled by custom settings and the value inside has more return reasons</span>
          </li>
          <li>On click of the 'Submit' button, case status is set to 'Pending Approval' and email is sent to the approver for approval.</li>
          <li>If no approver record is found, agent is notified by an error toast message.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
