  </ac:image>
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="ffccc74a-4ecb-4b74-84b8-381a678190cd" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Notes in Edit Scenario</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <ul>
      <li>For Exception Intake, when agent edits the case, he cannot increase the Return Quantity of any line item. He is only allowed to decrease it. In case the agent increases the Return Quantity of any line item, the 'Save' button is disabled and the agent is notified by an error message.</li>
      <li>In Edit Case scenario, for any line item, if the earlier entitlement check date is on the same day, we will not be doing the Entitlement check for that Line item again and we use earlier data; but if any new line items are added, then the Entitlement check API callout will happen for the newly added Line Items.</li>
      <li>If the case is being edited and the earlier line items have gone beyond the Credit Price Validation step and the earlier detected credit price is on the same day, then the credit price validation API call is bypassed for existing line items.</li>
    </ul>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.13. ">CPN Indicator Check</h2>
<ul>
  <li>When user clicks on 'Save &amp; View Summary' or 'Save for Later', an additional validation called 'CPN Indicator check' is done. For the selected Sold To CMF, the value of the 'Is CPN required?' field is fetched.</li>
  <li>If the field value is 'True', then all the line items are validated for CPN values.</li>
  <li>Any line item that doesn't have a CPN value is disabled and shown to the agent. The corresponding error message can be seen in the validation column for the disabled line items.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="b3201273-1d23-464d-b14d-92223997bf57" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
  <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
  <ac:rich-text-body>
    <p>For CPN Support Customer, if the CPN is not available for line items then the MMCPN API will be called on click of 'Save for Later' &amp; 'Save &amp; View Summary' buttons and will populate the CPN at line item level; otherwise the line items which do not have a CPN are disabled with an error message &amp; the User is not able to create a Case with non-CPN line items.</p>
  </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
